HEADWORD: Cholecystotomy
<hw>Chol`e*cys*tot"o*my</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Cholecystis</ets> + Gr. <grk>te`mnein</grk> to cut.]</ety>
<fld>(Surg.)</fld> <def>The operation of making an opening in the gall
bladder, as for the removal of a gallstone.</def>⟦br⟧
